mjerez.jmicrobench
Class BenchmarkRunner

java.lang.Object
  mjerez.jmicrobench.BenchmarkRunner

public class BenchmarkRunner
extends Object

Base class which runs the Benchmarks.
Call the run() method to run the benchmark, this method is synchronized which means only one benchmark can be running at the same time.
Set printPhase to true before start any benchmark to print a message to System.err when each phase begins and ends, use this function together with the java compiler flag -verbose, this can help you to identify which classes are loaded during each one of the phases.
To obtain a correct benchmark neither the garbage collector nor any other class must be loaded during the profiling phase.

Author:
mjerez
